Step 1 : Create the cart view
#orders/views.py
from django.shortcuts import render

def view_cart(request):
    # if you have cart logic, load it here
    # For now, just render a placeholder template
    return render(request, "order/cart.html")

Step 2 : Add URL for the cart
from django.urls import path
from . import views

urlpatterns = [
    path("cart/", views.view_cart, name="view_cart"),
]

from django.urls import path, include

urlpatterns = [
    path("", include("home.urls")), 
    path("orders/", include("orders.urls")),
]


Step 3 : Create cart template
{% extends "base.html" %}

{% block content %}
<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto p-6">
   <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Your Cart</h1>
   <p>Cart items will appear here.<p>
</div>
{% endblock %}

Step 4 : Add the "View Cart" link
<a href="{% url 'view_cart' %}"
   class="inline-block mt-4 px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-700 transition">
   View cart
</a>


Result::
> URL /orders/cart displays the cart page.
> Homepage/Menu page has a button linking to it.
> When your cart system is ready , you can fill in the logic inside
view.cart().
